		DORAND 3
			SAY Ohh, yes ... my mother always called it a pergola, but to Nujel'mites 'tis a gazebo.  Whatever thou'lt call it, it lies in the southeast quarter near the bank and the inn.
			SAY Dost thou mean the gazebo? The little open-air wooden structure on the southeast side of town? 'Tis between The Silver Bow tavern and Restful Slumber inn.
